The paper deals with the problem of channel state information in a multiple-input single-output (MISO) broadcast channel (BC), which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also considers the use of limited-capacity feedback links, which is a topic in networked systems (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper proposes novel communication protocols, which falls under the category of signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also deals with the issue of frequency correlated channels, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM) and communication engineering (cs.CE).
